# Session 5 (Jhonny Abou Rjeily)

## Implemented Features
The aim of this lab was to refactor the existing repository, by adding custom exceptions, custom validations, using generics and reflection, adding middlewares and filters,
and finally testing the implemented features.

1- Exceptions
In Warehouse.Application: NotFoundException
  --> Before adding this exception, if the handler does not find a resource, it returned null,
  now it returns a 404 Not Found response, that is later caught by the middleware.
  
In Warehouse.Domain: BusinessRuleException
   --> In the business rules inside the domain, most of the thrown exceptions were of the type "ArgumentException",
   however it is more convenient to state that it is a business rule exception, as it is concerned with the entities properties themselves.
   
These 2 Exceptions, in addition to other ones (of the general type Exception), are caught by the corresponding middleware.

2- Validation
The DTOs already contained Data Annotations, however I created a custom attribute to check whether the expiry date is valid.
It should be greater than the current date.

3- Generics
in Warehouse.Domain, I added a new class: "IRepository.cs", which is an interface that accepts a generic type T, 
and IProductRepository and ISupplierRepository implement it. This reduced the same code (same functions) that were repeated in
the 2 interfaces.

4-MiddleWares
The app now has 3 middlewares (in order)
RequestTimingMiddleware -> To measure how long each request takes.
CorrelationIdMiddleware -> To assign a unique Correlation ID to every request.
ExceptionHandlingMiddleware> -> This middleware catches the 3 exceptions listed above, and returns a common error response to the client.

5- Filters
2 filters were implemented:
ActionLoggingFilter   -> logs when an endpoint starts executing and when it finishes.
ModelValidationFilter -> checks that the model is valid

Note:
Middleware runs for every HTTP request before it reaches the controllers -> It is used for application-wide concerns.
Filters run only for MVC controller actions after the request reaches the MVC pipeline -> They are used for controller-specific concerns.

6-Reflection
An extra endpoint to the ProductsController was added to return the validation attributes of the properties of the DTO's
(in the Contracts folder in the Presentation layer)                  

7-Async Programming
The application was updated to use asynchronous methods throughout the controllers, handlers, repositories,
and Entity Framework operations. CancellationToken was also passed through all the async calls.

## Notes
Refer to the screenshots of swagger inside the screenshots folder (Session05 (Jhonny))

# Session 6 (Lea Noun)

## Implemented Features
The aim of this lab is to  improve reliability, maintainability, and performance, by implementing localization, caching, background jobs, logging and health checks.

### 1- Localization
- Added support for multiple languages using resource (`.resx`) files.
- Localized validation messages and API responses based on the `Accept-Language` request header, that was added to Swagger.

### 2- Caching
- Integrated Redis distributed caching to reduce database queries, and make the app faster.
- Cached products and suppliers, and automatically invalidated the cache when data was added or updated.

### 3- Background Jobs
- Integrated Hangfire to run a recurring background task that logs products whose expiry date is near.

### 4- Logging
- Integrated Serilog for structured logging.
- Logged API requests, application events, and background job execution.

### 5- Health Checks
- Added health checks for PostgreSQL and Redis, with a health-check UI.

## Bonus Challenges

### Challenge 1 – Background Job Improvement
- Enhanced the Hangfire background job to automatically archive products that have been expired for more than 7 days.
- Logged every product that was archived.

### Challenge 3 – Cache Statistics Endpoint
- Created an endpoint that returns cache statistics, including cached keys, cache hit count, cache miss count, and the last cache refresh time.

### Challenge 4 – Retry Health Check
- Implemented a custom Redis health check that retries the connection up to three times before reporting Redis as unhealthy.

## API endpoints added
### Cache
- `GET /api/cache/statistics` – To retrieve cache statistics (cached keys, hit/miss counts, and last refresh time).

### Health Checks
- `GET /health` – To view the health status of the application and its dependencies.
- `GET /health-ui` – To open the Health Checks UI dashboard.

### Background Jobs
- `/hangfire` – Open the Hangfire dashboard to monitor and manage recurring background jobs.

## Notes
- Challenge 2 was not implemented as I already had a middleware (RequestTimingMiddleware), that tracks the time it takes each endpoint to execute. 
- Screenshots are available in the screenshots folder.



